One thing that took a year or so for me to notice, or have the willingness to notice, was that my hips canât do something that Iâd like them to do: stretch out to the side. ð¤¸ð»ââï¸ The simple work of trying to control my jointsâdoing Kinstretchâhelped me see what was really going on.
//
\\
//
Now, I donât mean that I couldnât do the splits. Sure, thatâd be great to find some day, but first I needed to figure out how to get any sort of lateral freedom at all. @functionalrangeconditioning was instrumental in laying out the concepts, but the regular work of Kinstretch created the practice. After all, your body only speaks one language: #load . Speak to it often, especially your darker corners.
//
